<br />
  The Raid Enchanter part 2
<br />
« Thread started on: May 20th, 2003, 1:57pm »   
<br />

<br />
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
<br />
Preparation and knowledge is the key!!!
<br />

<br />
If in doubt ask ... first ask your enchanter channel about an encounter if yer not sure what to do... if they dont know..then ask a raidleader or officer..or someone knowledgable 
<br />

<br />
Enchanters really need to understand whats going on and how your contribution reflects on the whole... not just i need to keep these mobs mezzed for the next 20 mins...but why? how does this effect the raid... what are the tanks doing, what are the clerics doing, what are the pullers doing (bind sight is great for this) If you have to read spoilers off graffes or the safehouse... understand the encounter
<br />

<br />
MAPS! <a href="http://maps.eq-toolbox.com/" target="_blank">http://maps.eq-toolbox.com/</a>
<br />
dont get lost otw to a raid.. or when moving in raid... backspace opens up the map window, turn the height filter off, and use the scroll key in the middle of yer mouse to zoom in and out so you know where you are..and use your compass! all raid directions should be given in compass directions or clearly defined
<br />

<br />
Be on time for raids.. if the raid is at 6EST...that means buffs should be happening at 6EST not 620 ...not head to the raid zone at 6... theres nothing like sitting around on yer thumbs for an hour waiting for peeps to login and move there... if you know yer gonna be late... post on yer website to let them know, or tell an officer in game HEY work is running late i wont be on till 7est ok... (make sure to include the timezone yer in)
<br />

<br />
EQTRADERS storywindow! <a href="http://mboards.eqtraders.com/phpBB2/viewtopic.php?t=4105" target="_blank">http://mboards.eqtraders.com/phpBB2/viewtopic.php?t=4105</a> this is a bonus to yer guild to help you look up questions about what this or that drop does...
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.eqinterface.com/sdownload/fileinfo.php?id=844" target="_blank">http://www.eqinterface.com/sdownload/fileinfo.php?id=844</a> This is IMPORTANT
<br />
Its a target window/timer (analog timer) that counts ticks to 60 seconds... great for timing mez without having to click anything
<br />

<br />
Bag 1 (10 slot bag)
<br />
1x stack peridots
<br />
1x stack peridots
<br />
1x stack peridots
<br />
1x stack peridots
<br />
1x stack peridots
<br />
1x stack peridots
<br />
1x stack tiny coffins
<br />
1x stack pearls
<br />
1x stack star rubies 
<br />
1x stack emeralds
<br />

<br />
why carry all these spell components? because your raid needs them.and you need them ( I also carry cats eyes agates for my halo)
<br />

<br />
Bag 2 (10 slots)
<br />
1x stack good food
<br />
1x stack good water
<br />
1x stack food
<br />
1x stack water
<br />
1x stack food
<br />
1x stack water
<br />
enduring breath item
<br />
shrink item/potions
<br />
corpse locating rod
<br />
horse/lizard (even if cheap one for just medding)
<br />

<br />
also, have your invisibilty, see invis, self invis, enduring breath/leviathan eyes spells on a handy page .. mine are on page 14 (/book 14) and know how to access it... keep your main spells you use on page 1-4 so they are easy to access
<br />

<br />
Spell lineup (varies on situation)
<br />
1) Tash (this should always be up)
<br />
2) Bliss/mez (this should always be up)
<br />
3) Charm/Utility slot (depends if charming is viable in that raid/zone)
<br />
4) group haste (this is the most common buff... i always keep it up)
<br />
5) arcane rune (or its equivalent for yer level)
<br />
6) boggle (yes it works... use it..learn it... love it, should always be up)
<br />
7) Utility (usually a nuke or a deagro spell for the clerics or for myself if im main tasher)
<br />
<img src="images/smiles/icon_cool.gif" alt="Cool" border="0" /> Clarity spell (can be switched out in most situations thankfully because of clarity duration)
<br />

<br />
Always try to keep your spells in the same slots so you can use the Alt-# to activate them if your blind or need to use them... keep tash on a hotkey as you will probly cast that more then any other spell ever..
<br />
Have a hotkey for haste becuase of the low duration on it and the tendency for tanks to go splat<br />_________________<br />Agatha - Tauren Shaman - Azjol-Nerub
<br />
Murdoch - Undead Priest - Azjol-Nerub</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
